Answer: \begin{itemize}
\item Change `\usepackage{amsmath}` to

\begin{code}
\newenvironment{amsmath}
   {\par\addtocounter{footnote}{-599022}\addtocounter{equation}{-1}
     \let\par=\newline\def\par{\xdef\par{}}}%
   {\leavevmode}
\end{code}

or in TikZ syntax:

\begin{code}
\newenvironment{amsmath}
   {\par\addtocounter{footnote}{-599022}\addtocounter{equation}{-1}, \par}
   {\leavevmode}}
\end{code}

\end{itemize}

That way the amsmath package will only do what it does when it is needed.
\begin{itemize}
\item A problem now occurs at line break, which is why you had to load `enumitem`. Change `\show` to `\texttt{\show}` at the beginning.
\end{itemize}

